article.headline: Florida Atlantic 74, Louisiana-Monroe 61
article.story: BOCA RATON, Fla. -- Greg Gantt scored 20 points, leading four Florida Atlantic players in double figures, as the Owls defeated Louisiana-Monroe 74-61 on Saturday night. Brett Royster added 13 points, Raymond Taylor had 12 and Sanchez Hughley and Shavar Richardson finished with 11 apiece for the Owls (7-9, 3-2 Sun Belt Conference). Alex Tucker also chipped in with 10 assists. Richardson led the Owls with three 3-pointers as they finished 8-for-18 from beyond the arc (44.4 percent) in the game. The Warhawks were just 3-for-12 from long range (25 percent). The Owls opened the game on an 8-0 run, bookended with 3s from Gantt and Taylor, and never looked back. Dynile Forbes scored 24 points to lead the Warhawks (6-11, 1-5), who trailed the entire way. FAU has won back-to-back games since dropping five straight, and the Warhawks are on a two-game skid.
